Due to expected severe weather and snowfall throughout the night and early morning. We have made the decision to have Monday, February 3rd be a late start. School will start at 10:30. If your student rides the bus they need to be at trax no later than 10:00. We will know in the morning if we need to cancel school all together. We will notify parents if there are any changes as soon as possible.

Parents are also reminded that they may keep their students at home if they it is unsafe for their student to travel to school.

We would like to invite you to a screening of the documentary "The S-Word". Following the screening, our school social worker, Braxton Dutson, will lead a discussion about suicide prevention and provide resources for parents, students, and families. Suicide and mental health conditions have an impact on just about everyone, whether directly or through someone we love. Please join us for an empowering evening focused on hope and support.

Date: Tuesday, May 21
Time: 5 - 7 pm
Location: East Hollywood High School

All free and reduced applications need to be done online through Aspire.

complete application

UTA is changing its schedules on April 8, 2018. Due to the implementation of federally-mandated Positive Train Control (safety measures established by the U.S. Department of Transportation) requirements on its commuter rail system, UTA will be adjusting its FrontRunner schedule. This change requires UTA to make scheduling adjustments throughout its system in order to preserve connections and transfers. As a result, all TRAX schedules and nearly all bus schedules will be adjusted starting April 8.

More information is available here: rideuta.com/news/2018/03/Extensive-Rail-and-Bus-Changes-Coming-in-April. In Addition, UTA's Trip Planner and Customer Service department are available to assist you in planning your trip so that you can be prepared to get where you need to go when the changes take effec

post_text:
The ASVAB test is going to be administered here at East Hollywood High on Thursday, March 23rd, 2017. The test will take place in the library. The start time is 8:30. We encourage all students to consider taking this career exploration test which may help you gain an understanding of your aptitudes and perhaps aid in exploring future career choices. 10th 11th and 12th graders are encouraged to take this test; however it is strictly voluntary.

The ASVAB is a multiple-aptitude battery that measures developed abilities and helps predict future academic and occupational success in the military. It is administered annually to more than one million military applicants, high school, and post-secondary students.

If you are interested please see Carla in the front office.

East Hollywood High School students (including current Seniors) who meet the following requirements are eligible to attend the All American High School Film Festival on October 7-9, 2016:

post_text:
The ASVAB test is going to be administered here at EHHS on Tuesday, March 8, 2016. The test will take place in the library. The start time is 8:30.

Students are encouraged to consider taking this career exploration test which may help them gain an understanding of their aptitudes and perhaps aid in exploring future career choices.

10th 11th and 12th graders are encouraged to take this test; however it is strictly voluntary.

The ASVAB is a multiple-aptitude battery that measures developed abilities and helps predict future academic and occupational success in the military. It is administered annually to more than one million military applicants, high school, and post-secondary students.

Any questions please see Petra

post_text:
This message is in regards to the East Hollywood High School field trip to New York City for the All American High School Film Festival.

Please disregard this message if you are a new student.

This is a reminder that all requirements to attend the festival must be submitted tomorrow, Tuesday, Sep 1. This is a non-flexible deadline as we will be purchasing airline tickets and hotels on Wednesday morning.

As a reminder, the requirements you need to submit are the following:
A check made out to East Hollywood High School for $1500 to cover airfare, hotels, and festival tickets.
Printed proof that your attendance is at 95% or higher for the 5th and 6th term of the last school year.
Printed proof that you have a 3.0 GPA for 6th term of the last school year.
Printed proof that a film you worked on was submitted to the festival.
Please deliver all of these materials to Will McAllister during the school day tomorrow.

post_text:
In October 2015, East Hollywood High School will take a field trip to New York City to participate in the All American High School Film Festival. All students who attend will need to meet certain criteria and raise a designated amount of money. Students who graduate this year are eligible to go if they meet the criteria.

As part of the Parent-Teacher Conference held on Thursday, March 26, Will McAllister and Josh Wagner will hold a meeting at 5:30 in the library. All students who want to go to New York City need to be at this meeting with one of their parents in order to go on the trip. At the meeting, the criteria and expenses related to the trip will be explained.

If you have any questions or have no way of attending this meeting, please email Josh Wagner at jwagner@ehhs.us.

text: Yesterday was a great day! Our open house at East Hollywood High School was revitalizing for me. I so enjoyed seeing former students. I think there was a smile on my face the entire time. And, then, later in the day, Greg and I went to visit Randall Lake's studio downtown in the Guthrie building. His work is beautiful. He very generously gave me a print of "Rococo Punk," a beautiful painting that I saw years ago on the cover of a local weekly magazine. Thank you, Randall Lake!

Post-production is happening as we speak. Be prepared for the most amazing webseries experience you will ever have.

The script, the art, the cast, the crew (minus two of us old fogey teachers, and a couple of supporting adult characters) - all done by high school students. Incredibly talent high school students, might I add.

More Paradise teasers to come!
